# OpenSpec + Beads workflow (SmartCope)



Full cycle: **OpenSpec (What) → Beads (How) → Code**. See `AGENTS.md`.



## Golden path



1. `/opsx:propose <id>` or `/opsx:ff <id>` — create artifacts under `openspec/changes/<id>/`

2. User reviews and says **Go!**

3. `/openspec-to-beads <id>` — Beads epic + one task per `##` phase in `tasks.md`; writes `beads-map.md`

4. `/opsx:apply <id>` — work only from `bd ready`; `bd close` then sync `tasks.md` checkboxes

5. `/opsx:verify <id>` → `/opsx:archive <id>`



## Source of truth



| Phase | Owner |

|-------|-------|

| Requirements / design | OpenSpec artifacts (`proposal`, `specs`, `design`, `adr/`) |

| What to do next | **Beads** (`bd ready`) |

| Progress mirror | `tasks.md` checkboxes (sync on `bd close`) |



## Do not



- Jump from propose/ff straight to `/opsx:apply` without `/openspec-to-beads`

- Tick `tasks.md` without `bd close` on the matching phase

- Use TodoWrite or speckit-style task lists for implementation (Beads only)

- Use TodoWrite during `/opsx:apply` — only allowed during artifact creation in propose/ff



## Context loading (tiered)



- **Always on apply:** `bd ready`, `bd show <id>`, pending lines in `tasks.md`, `beads-map.md`

- **When needed:** relevant `specs/**/spec.md` section, `adr/` soundbite

- **Skip by default:** full `proposal.md`, entire `design.md` if ADRs cover it



Stack and schema: `openspec/config.yaml`, `adr/README.md`, `docs/database_overall_v2.md`

